3 SECTION 3. G.S. 65-62 reads as rewritten:
4 "§ 65-62. Individual contracts for care and maintenance.
5 At the time of making a sale or receiving the initial deposit hereunder, the cemetery company
6 shall deliver to the person to whom such sale is made, or who makes such deposit, an instrument
7 in writing which shall specifically state that the net income of the care and maintenance trust
8 fund shall be used solely for the care and maintenance of the cemetery, for reasonable costs of
9 administering such care and maintenance and for reasonable costs of administering the trust fund.
10 Within 60 days after the end of the calendar or fiscal year of the cemetery company, the cemetery
11 company shall furnish adequate reports with the details of the care and maintenance work
12 performed on forms provided by the Commission."".
